          "body": "Verses 8-19 are a comprehensive catalogue of priestly revenue: the most holy gifts reserved from the fire (grain offerings, sin offerings, guilt offerings — eaten by male priests only in holy space, 18:9-10); wave offerings eaten by any clean household member (18:11); firstfruits of oil, wine, and grain (18:12-13); devoted things (18:14); the redemption price for firstborn humans (five shekels, 18:16) and firstborn unclean animals; the meat of firstborn clean animals after their blood and fat are offered (18:17-18). The list is exhaustive by design — God is making clear that nothing is left to ad hoc arrangement. The provision is then sealed with the chapter's most solemn language: 'It is an everlasting covenant of salt before the LORD to you and your descendants' (18:19). Salt in the ancient Near East was the preservative that prevented decay — the covenant of salt is the covenant that cannot rot. God's provision for the priesthood is as permanent as His commitment to Israel."
